					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Anyway, now that I've told you why you're going to find it difficult, to directly answer your question, try using a 74'138 hooked up as follows:<br /><br />A15 - /G2a<br />A14 - G1<br />A13 - /G2b<br />A12 - A<br />A11 - B<br />R/W - C<br />microcontroller /Interrupt input - /Y0<br /><br />This will let you know any time the 2A03 is writing to $4000-$47FF. <br /><br />Then again, given that <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=82795#p82795" class="postlink">someone managed to implement UNROM using an attiny</a>, maybe that's all you need.</div>

